author: pburba
msg: Follow-up to r1101578 and r1101635: Take better advantage of iterpools and
subpools.
Suggested by: gstein
* subversion/libsvn_client/merge.c
(populate_remaining_ranges): Destroy iterpool before early return.  Use
iterpool in place of scratch_pool where possible since we already have
it and don't know how long the caller provided scratch pool will live.
(record_skips,
normalize_merge_sources,
do_file_merge,
do_merge,
calculate_left_hand_side): Create iterpool earlier and/or defer its
destruction until later and use it in place of the caller provided
scratch pool.
(merge_cousins_and_supplement_mergeinfo): Use a subpool in place of the
scratch pool for allocating some short-lived block-local variables.
